comment:
* Represents the codec status (configuration and capability) for a Bluetooth A2DP source device.
 *
 * @see BluetoothA2dp

variables.name: EXTRA_CODEC_STATUS
variables.comment:
* Extra for the codec configuration intents of the individual profiles. * *

This extra represents the current codec status of the A2DP profile.

methods.name: private static boolean sameCapabilities(@Nullable List<BluetoothCodecConfig> c1, @Nullable List<BluetoothCodecConfig> c2)
methods.comment:
* Checks whether two lists of capabilities contain same capabilities. The order of the
     * capabilities in each list is ignored.
     *
     * @param c1 the first list of capabilities to compare
     * @param c2 the second list of capabilities to compare
     * @return {@code true} if both lists contain same capabilities

methods.name: public boolean isCodecConfigSelectable(@Nullable BluetoothCodecConfig codecConfig)
methods.comment:
* Checks whether the codec config matches the selectable capabilities. Any parameters of the
     * codec config with NONE value will be considered a wildcard matching.
     *
     * @param codecConfig the codec config to compare against
     * @return {@code true} if the codec config matches, {@code false} otherwise

methods.name: public int hashCode()
methods.comment: Returns a hash based on the codec config and local capabilities.

methods.name: public String toString()
methods.comment: * Returns a {@link String} that describes each BluetoothCodecStatus parameter current value.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)
methods.comment:
* Flattens the object to a parcel.
     *
     * @param out The Parcel in which the object should be written
     * @param flags Additional flags about how the object should be written

methodNames: private static boolean sameCapabilities(@Nullable List<BluetoothCodecConfig> c1, @Nullable List<BluetoothCodecConfig> c2)
public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)
